Document: PhysicsBody3D
Path: godot/classes/class_physicsbody3d.rst
Summary: Describes the methods available for PhysicsBody3D nodes in Godot Engine.

Method: add_collision_exception_with(body: Node)
Adds a collision exception with the specified body.

Method: get_axis_lock(axis: BodyAxis) → bool
Returns whether the specified axis is locked.

Method: get_collision_exceptions() → Array[PhysicsBody3D]
Returns an array of all bodies that have collision exceptions.

Method: get_gravity() → Vector3
Returns the gravity vector applied to the body.

Method: move_and_collide(motion: Vector3, test_only: bool = false, safe_margin: float = 0.001, recovery_as_collision: bool = false, max_collisions: int = 1) → KinematicCollision3D
Moves the body along the given motion vector, handling collisions. Returns a KinematicCollision3D object if a collision occurred.

Method: remove_collision_exception_with(body: Node)
Removes a collision exception with the specified body.

Method: set_axis_lock(axis: BodyAxis, lock: bool)
Locks or unlocks the specified axis for the body.

Method: test_move(from: Transform3D, motion: Vector3, collision: KinematicCollision3D = null, safe_margin: float = 0.001, recovery_as_collision: bool = false, max_collisions: int = 1) → bool
Tests if a move along the given motion vector would result in a collision, without actually moving the body. If a collision occurs, information about it is stored in the `collision` object.
